HEADWORD: Gena
<hw>Ge"na</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <ety>[L., the cheek.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The cheek; the feathered side of
the under mandible of a bird.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The part of the
head to which the jaws of an insect are attached.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

